## Introduction
The Action Framework is a versatile tool for guiding and refining interactions with language models. Whether you are a beginner or an experienced programmer, this guide provides a comprehensive, step-by-step approach to generating effective prompts.

## Understanding the Action Framework

### Brainstorm + Action Word
The first step is to brainstorm ideas and select an action word that represents the main objective of your prompt. This action word will capture the essence of what you want the model to do.

```python
# Action Word
action_word = input("Enter the action word: ")
# Context
purpose = input("Enter the purpose of your prompt: ")
audience = input("Enter the target audience: ")
special_details = input("Enter any special details or circumstances: ")

# Prioritize
tone = input("Enter the desired tone of the response: ")
style = input("Enter the preferred style: ")
specific_elements = input("Enter specific elements to include or exclude: ")
# Evaluate and Refine
response = input("Enter the generated response: ")
# Evaluate the response and make necessary refinements to the prompt
